race.comment: HEWILLDOUS (3) resumed a big CL1 winner over 1213m and there was a stack of merit in the effort. Settled back off the wide gate and covered plenty of ground. Has the inside gate today and the longer sprint suits. With the extra fitness he can take the next step. LADY NEGRONI (9) has scored at her last two starts most recently over 1350m at Toodyay as favourite. Has a wide gate to contend with but is sure to go well again. QUEEN'S SACRIFICE (8) resumed with a strong placing at Toodyay and then was slow to recover at York and forgive. She has more up her sleeve and has plenty to weight relief this grade with a 3kg claim atop. Will push forward from the wide barrier and a much better effort is likely. MOMBASA (1) resumes and has won fresh. In the mix if presented on song.
